The paper discusses Voronoi diagrams and their variations, which are commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses properties related to measure concentration, which is a topic in probability theory and machine learning (cs.MG). The paper involves a decomposition of space into regions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorial geometry (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the existence of a neutral region, which is a concept related to the topology of the space, and thus falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
